## New Project: pyre
- **Replaces:** log4js (~7.4M weekly npm downloads, 5.8k GitHub stars, 4,183 dependents, single npm maintainer csausdev, last release v6.9.1 over 3 years ago, 83 open issues with zero maintainer responses, 15 unmerged PRs, issue #1440 "When will the new version be released?" unanswered)
- **Why:** Unmaintained 3+ years. log4js2 (@log4js2/core) exists but 6 years stale. Winston/pino/bunyan have completely different APIs — NOT drop-in replacements.
- **Package:** @agentine/pyre (verified available on npm)
- **Features:** Full log4js API: configure(), getLogger(), shutdown(), addLayout(), connectLogger(). Built-in appenders (stdout, stderr, console, file, dateFile, multiFile, logLevelFilter, categoryFilter, noLogFilter, recording, tcp). Built-in layouts (basic, colored, pattern, json, messagePassThrough, dummy). Category hierarchy with dot-separated level inheritance. Clustering/PM2 support. TypeScript-first, zero dependencies, ESM+CJS dual package, Node.js 18+. Log4js compat layer at pyre/compat/log4js.
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #920 (scaffolding), #921 (core types/levels/config), #922 (Logger + appenders), #923 (layouts/clustering/middleware/compat), #924 (tests + CI + release)

